						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab lying in the Hanumantadēva temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṁghaṇa—A.D. 1201.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">3rd year</hi> of the reign of <hi rend="bold">Siṁgaṇadēva, Durmati, Pushya ba. Amāvāsyā, Monday.</hi> The date is irregular. The given <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1201, December 27, Thursday.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a gift of tolls made by <hi rend="italic">Suṁkadadhikāri</hi> <hi rend="bold">Kācharasa.</hi> A division of <hi rend="bold">Fifty</hi> (name lost) in <hi rend="bold">Tardavāḍi One-Thousand</hi> is mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
